Text: since you individually included all the files in the torrent, the list is the actualy files themselves. kudos for doing this btw and not just raring them all up into a bunch. Doing it this way not only allows people to chose or not chose to download what they want, but it also, as you mentioned allows them to see whats in it. Now of course comes the sucky part. you have to seed until at least a few people have this all 100%. for 4 gigs thats alot of dedication if you have a semi low speed line, but congrats on doing it.

I plan to seed this thing for a very long time, or until there are many other seeds. Sadly, my DSL only allows a max upload of about 80 kbps. Plus, now I can point my buddies to this instead of having to burn discs. I must have burned this collection 200 times by now.

Strange no one bothered to mention that most of the songs are encoded at 64-96kbit.

That's because that was the bit rate available on most of the albums when i found them back in the old Napster days. However, let's not pretend that 96 is 30. They sound fine. I get bloody sick and tired of LIARS who pretend that they and Batman are capable of hearing the pitch differentials at 320 kbps. Even if you had superhero hearing, you'd need the sound system from G-d to be able to play something at that quality. I doubt if your ear buds on the iPod are capable of reaching that quality level.
